[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The argmax-vs-argmax F1 is a reasonable sanity-check metric, but it does not reflect how the model is actually used: multiplying its full distribution by volume to produce per-ESI counts. A model that predicts `{esi_3: 0.51, esi_4: 0.49}` and the actual hour has `{esi_3: 0.52, esi_4: 0.48}` looks identical to a model that predicts `{esi_3: 0.99, esi_4: 0.01}` under argmax F1, even though one is operationally fine and the other will badly miscount ESI 4 visits.
