[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Fix:** Either (a) replace the F1 macro with a multinomial log-loss against shares so the pseudocode and the Python agree:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import math
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m total_logloss = 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m total_n       = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m for row in validation:
