[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             total_logloss -= c * math.log(p)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             total_n       += c
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m acuity_logloss = total_logloss / total_n if total_n else float("nan")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m and report `acuity_logloss` instead of `acuity_macro_f1`; or (b) update the pseudocode in the main recipe to say "macro-F1 against the dominant ESI per row" so the artifacts agree. Option (a) is more truthful to what the model is doing and aligns with what production teams would actually monitor.
